node.text:
Chicken Pasta Salad and a chance to win a $250 WALMART gift card! #ad 

I’ve teamed up with @walmart and @worldfoodchampionships to create this chicken pasta bowl. Join in on the fun and enter for a chance to win! Get your inspiration on www.walmart.com/cookingchallenge to learn more about the rules and post your creation on FB and instagram using the hashtag #walmartcookingchallenge. Good luck! 

Chicken Pasta Salad Recipe 
Serve 4 

* 2 Boneless Skinless Chicken Breasts, diced 
* 1 Tbsp Olive Oil
* 1 tbsp lemon pepper 
* 1 tsp salt 
* 8 oz whole grain pasta, or gluten-free
* 1 Cup Cherry Tomatoes halved
* 1/4 cup corn 
* 1/4 cup shredded cheese 
* 1/4 Cup Green Olives sliced in half
* 2 cups fresh chopped spinach 

Dressing:
* 2 Tbsp Extra Virgin Olive Oil
* 2 Tbsp White Wine Vinegar
* 1 tbsp Honey
* 1 tbsp oregano 
* 2 tsp thyme 
* 1 Garlic Cloves pressed or minced
* 1 tsp salt 
* 1/2 tsp pepper 

Directions 
1-  Sauté the diced chicken with olive oil, lemon pepper and salt. Set aside 
2- Cook pasta according to package directions 
3- Meanwhile, chop and setup the other ingredients and make the salad dressing. 
4- Add everything in a large bowl and too with the salad dressing and mix well. 
5- Serve and enjoy!
.
Link in my profile for more details 
https://bit.ly/37IwwPL

node.text:
Crispy Baked Chicken Cutlets
.
Ingredients
1.5 lbs Chicken Breasts (about 4) skinless, boneless
1 Tsp Italian Seasoning
1 Tbsp Olive Oil
1 Large Egg
2 Tbsp Milk
¾ Cup Panko or italian style panko
¼ Cup Fresh Grated Parmesan Cheese
1 Tsp Garlic Powder
1 Tsp Smoked Paprika
Sea salt and pepper, to taste
Avocado cooking oil spray
1 Tbsp Fresh Chopped Parsley
.
Instructions
To prepare the cutlets, pound each chicken breast to an even 1/4 inch thickness.
Next, rub the chicken with Italian seasoning, salt, pepper and olive oil. If time allows, marinate it for 1h to overnight. This will give you the most tender and moist chicken.
Preheat your oven to 400°F and line a rimmed baking sheet with parchment paper. In a large bowl, whisk together the egg, milk, a pinch of salt and pepper.
In a shallow dish, combine the garlic powder, panko with parmesan and smoked paprika. Dip the chicken cutlets into the egg mixture, then dredge it into the panko mixture, lightly pressing to coat
Place the chicken onto the prepared baking sheet and spray with cooking oil spray. Bake in preheated oven for 15 minutes, then flip the chicken cutlets and bake for 5-8minutes more, or until golden and cooked through.
Sprinkle with fresh chopped parsley, and serve immediately.
.

Click the link in my profile for the recipe
https://healthyfitnessmeals.com/crispy-baked-chicken-cutlets/

node.text:
Loving my @litehousefoods Purely Balanced Tzatziki Ranch Greek Yogurt Dressing served with this Greek Chicken Meal Prep Salad. With only 45 calories per serving, 0g added sugar and gluten-free, you can now enjoy your salad without compromising on taste and quality. @litehousefoods Purely Balanced Greek Yogurt Dressings come in a convenient 9oz squeeze bottle and are available in five thick and creamy, Greek yogurt-based flavors. #ad #litehousefoods #litehousepurelybalanced
.
Simple and easy Greek-style meal prep chicken salad that’s nutritious, full of flavor, loaded with protein, and served with Litehouse Purely Balanced Tzatziki Ranch Greek Yogurt Dressing.
.
Visit litehousefoods.com/newpurelybalanced to find Purely Balanced in a store near you! Link in my profile. 
.
Serves 2, and can easily be doubled

Ingredients
For the chicken:
2 boneless and skinless chicken breasts
2 tbsp olive oil, divided
1 tsp thyme
1 tsp oregano
1-2 garlic cloves
1/2 lemon, juiced
Salt and pepper to taste

For the salad:
1 Romaine Lettuce, chopped
1/4 cup kalamata olives
1-2 cucumbers, peeled and chopped
1/2 cup cherry tomatoes
1/2 or 1 small purple onion
1/2 cup Feta Cheese, cubed
1 tbsp fresh dill, to garnish
1/4 cup @litehousefoods Purely Balanced Tzatziki Ranch Greek Yogurt Dressing

Instructions
1- Add the chicken breast to a Ziplock bag along with 1 tablespoon of olive oil, thyme, garlic, oregano, lemon, and salt and pepper. Let it marinate for 10-15 minutes in the fridge.
2- Over medium heat, add the remaining tablespoon of oil to a skillet or griddle. Grill the
chicken breast for 3-4 minutes on each side.
3-Once the chicken is cooked through, place on a plate and set it aside.
4-Assemble all the salad ingredients into a meal prep bowl. Starting with the romaine lettuce.
Top with sliced grilled chicken breast and serve with a side of @litehousefoods Purely Balanced Tzatziki Ranch Greek Yogurt Dressing.
